es.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.275065151&amp;id=F21H">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="R1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Dawson</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">IM</span></span>, Cornes JS, Morson BC. Primary malignant tumors of the intestinal tract. <em>Br J Surg</em>1961;49:80–89.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/bjs.18004921319">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/13884035/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Br+J+Surg&amp;publication_year=1961&amp;pages=80&amp;doi=10.1002%2Fbjs.18004921319&amp;pmid=13884035">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">2.</div><div id="R2" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Yoo</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">CC</span></span>, Levine MS, McLarney JK, Rubesin SE, Herlinger H. Value of barium studies for predicting primary versus secondary non-Hodgkin’s gastrointestinal lymphoma. <em>Abdom Imaging</em>2000;25: 368–372.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s002610000055">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/10926188/">PubMed</a></di