<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">27</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">5</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Sep 1 2007</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1371</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1388</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17848697/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">17848697</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2007.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Sep 1 2007</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.275065151">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=AIDS+%3D+acquired+immunodeficiency+syndrome&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">AIDS = acquired immunodeficiency syndrome</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=H-E+%3D+hematoxylineosin&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">H-E = hematoxylineosin</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=HIV+%3D+human+immunodeficiency+virus&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">HIV = human immunodeficiency virus</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MALT+%3D+mucosa-associated+lymphoid+tissue&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MALT = mucosa-associated lymphoid tissue</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The incidence and pathogenesis, pathologic features, staging, and radiologic appearances of primary gastrointestinal lymphomas are discussed and illustrated.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Sangeet</span> <span property="familyName">Ghai</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD, FRCR</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departments of Medical Imaging (Sangeet G., J.P., Sandeep G.) and Histopathology (M.S.), University Hospital of North Staffordshire NHS Trust, Keele University, Stoke-on-Trent, England; and the Division of Abdominal Imaging, Department of Medical Imaging, University Health Network and Mount Sinai Hospital, University of Toronto, 585 University Ave, NCSB 1C544, Toronto, ON, Canada M5G 2N2 (Sangeet G., M.E.O., K.K.). Recipient of a Certificate of Merit award for an education exhibit at the 2005 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received August 11, 2006; revision requested November 9 and received December 15; accepted December 15. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Ghai/Sangeet" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">John</span> <span property="familyName">Pattison</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">FRCR</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations